<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no">
  <title><%= @page_title %></title>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
  <%= csp_meta_tag %>

  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
  <%= javascript_pack_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
</head>

<body>
<p class="notice"><%= notice %></p>
<p class="alert"><%= alert %></p>

<%# we can define partial view like this. In partial views we have to write filename by starting _ but in defining
we should write without _%>
<%# and we can pass data to partial view like this. %>
<%= render "shared/nav", location: "top" %>

<%# and here we can define view helper. The difference is generally we dont write inside of view helpers html.
Generally we use helpers for razor operations.(like if else or case statements) %>
<%= login_helper %>

<%= yield %>
<%= @copyright %>
<%# and also we can pass parameters to view helpers %>
<%= source_helper("application") %>
</body>
</html>
